I"<p>‚ÄúEvery Church Shall Burn‚Äù was kinda the ‚Äòbastard child‚Äô of the first six songs that Stan/Dementor sent me in Summer of 2001. As you can see from the lyrics, they don‚Äôt scan in a regular rhythm, there are odd line counts, and the overly-long repeated section doesn‚Äôt really lend itself well to what we would think of as a chorus. As I described before, I left this one for last, and so it‚Äôs the only one of those first six that Dementor never did a demo of - though he tried, and based on what I ended up writing it was confusing on paper because I distinctly remember him emailing me and saying he wasn‚Äôt sure what I wanted him to do with it.</p>

